[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Generating a 3D model with AI is easy now,&nbsp; but rigging and animating without spending&nbsp;&nbsp; hours of manual work is still a big issue.&nbsp; Luckily, there\'s now a new completely local&nbsp;&nbsp; and free tool called Mesh to Motion that lets&nbsp; you drop in any model, auto rigid in seconds,&nbsp;&nbsp; and lets you pick the animations you want and&nbsp; export it then straight into Blender or Unreal.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I\'m going to show you how to one-click install&nbsp; the tool, upload your own 3D model, and how to&nbsp;&nbsp; use it effectively. So, let\'s get into it. Hey&nbsp; guys, and welcome back to the channel. As always,&nbsp;&nbsp; my name is Philip from Pixel Artistry, and today&nbsp; I\'m going to show you the tool Mesh to Motion,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'which is incredibly easy to install. It can serve&nbsp; as a local mixer more alternative basically,&nbsp;&nbsp; and it\'s really straightforward. So, let me show&nbsp; you quickly what it is. You can think of it as the&nbsp;&nbsp; missing step in a fully local pipeline. So you&nbsp; can generate for example then a model with TRIS&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '2 or Pixel 3D bring it then in here and you walk&nbsp; out with a rigged and animated character without&nbsp;&nbsp; touching any paid services for the rigging and&nbsp; animation part. And we can also see here on their&nbsp;&nbsp; website basically that you can animate animals,&nbsp; monsters and humans which is of course really&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'cool and you have a full 3D animation library and&nbsp; autorigging tools that we can then use. Here are&nbsp;&nbsp; also some examples of it. So we have three ways&nbsp; actually to use it. So we can either you know use&nbsp;&nbsp; pre-made animations, we can also upload our own&nbsp; 3D model or we can even use like pre-wig models&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'so that you upload your own rigged character and&nbsp; then animate it. Another really cool feature is&nbsp;&nbsp; of course that Mesh tootion also provides all&nbsp; the Blender models and animation files for you&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to study and improve. So you can basically go in&nbsp; their library and then see how they build up the&nbsp;&nbsp; rigs and so on. And you can even improve or add&nbsp; new animations from the Blender rigs that are&nbsp;&nbsp; provided because this whole project is completely&nbsp; open source and is running under an MIT license&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'which is of course amazing because this means&nbsp; that we can use it commercially as well and you&nbsp;&nbsp; can use it for your own games without having any&nbsp; doubt that you have to take care of any license&nbsp;&nbsp; and so on. And of course this is built for the&nbsp; open source community. So feel welcome to also&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'contribute to it to improve the tool of course&nbsp; and give feedback for example also on the Discord. So to run the tool we have actually two options.&nbsp; So one is that we can directly try it out on the&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'website without installing anything which is kind&nbsp; of the easiest way. So you just have to click on&nbsp;&nbsp; the website that I\'m going to link you down below.&nbsp; You can just click here on try it out and then&nbsp;&nbsp; basically we already have here the interface and&nbsp; you will see that it\'s very easy to use. We have&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'human animations, but we also have a fox here&nbsp; with different animation for basically each rig&nbsp;&nbsp; character. We even have bird animations, which I&nbsp; think is cool for fly cycles and so on. And you&nbsp;&nbsp; can also have a rest pose or him walking.&nbsp; And this is for multiple characters. So,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
